    <briefdescription>
<para>One DCS-BIOS digit source feeding a <ref refid="structOpenSkyhawk_1_1DrumReadout" kindref="compound">DrumReadout</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Populate <computeroutput>address</computeroutput> / <computeroutput>mask</computeroutput> from the A_4E_C_* and A_4E_C_*_AM constants in <ref refid="A4EC__OutputIds_8h" kindref="compound">A4EC_OutputIds.h</ref>. The masked value (0..mask) is scaled to nDigits decimal digits: digits = round((value &amp; mask) / mask * (10^nDigits − 1)); each of those nDigits digits is spliced into the readout&apos;s combined number starting at <computeroutput>place</computeroutput> (0 = least-significant column). </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
